track_notes: 1/2 mile of off trail not to difficult

I chose to do a long hike (about 14 miles total) and activated 7358 first, then picked up Mount Peeley on the return to the trailhead.  Park at Mount Peeley Trailhead, which is at the end of a long dirt road (high clearance or 4wd necessary).  On the bushwhack portion of the Mount Peeley summit, there is a cairn marking a light trail that leads up to a campsite.  After that you will need to find your own route, there are various cairns along the way up but no real defined trail.
track_title: Double Activation 7358 Peak and Mount Peeley via AZT
